                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d382">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">814.00/632: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Curtis</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Guatemala</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-01-22T22:00:00-07:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 22, 1922—10 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received January 23—8:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>9. Convention of the Liberal Party this afternoon nominated Orellana. Ubico<note
                        n="2" xml:id="d382fn2">General Ubico, also, had been a candidate for the
                        nomination.</note> had previously pledged adherence to the decision of the
                    convention.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Curtis</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
